text: Kazakhstan, Russia and Canada have each seen their share of the global hash rate increase over the past year. Data from Cambridge recorded precisely 0% of bitcoin's hash rate coming from China in July of 2021, marking an abrupt about face for a country that used to be a mining powerhouse. For context, in August of 2020, China miners made up 67.1% of bitcoin's hash rate. As recently as May of 2021, China still accounted for 34.3%. In a similar move, Coinbase, the larger exchange by far in this story, announced a waitlist for Coinbase NFT.
